 AUC in each task,
 so we can legitimately assess holdout performance on unseen studies.
 For cancer diagnosis,
 SVM achieves the best holdout performance,
 followed by random forest and KNN.
 For cancer type,
 KNN leads on holdout,
 followed by random forest and SVM.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The gap between in-study test and holdout is again large for cancer type,
 but UC/CAP with KNN achieves substantially higher cancer type holdout AUC than any tetramer-based classifier,
 demonstrating that richer within-run compositional features partially attenuate the study-level shortcut problem.
\end_layout

